title: Cats skipper loses license in speeding incident
text:
Geelong captain Joel Selwood loses license for speeding incident February 25, 2017 11:57am Source: FOX SPORTS GEELONG captain Joel Selwood could face further punishment from the AFL club after being caught speeding at 127km/h on Friday. 
Selwood, an Australian Grand Prix ambassador, will lose his license for one month after he was booked in a 100km/h zone. 
“Joel and the club are disappointed in his actions,” acting Cats chief executive Justin Reeves said in a statement. 
“Everyone associated with the club takes road safety very seriously, and knows that speeding is unacceptable and can cause accidents. 
“Fortunately these actions did not result in an accident.” 
Cats management will meet with the Traffic Accident Commission this week to discuss any further penalties that they could impose on the star midfielder, who informed the club immediately after being caught. 
— WITH AAP
